"CS Minor" can help to be a software engineer?

I am DS major but I changed my career plan to be a software engineer. 

I think i don't have time to double major because i am already senior, but i can do cs minor before graduation. I know that my coding skill is much more important to be hired as a software engineer but if i do cs minor and take some more upper cs class can help me with my job hiring? or is it waste my time? 

Any thought and any suggestion and any experience can help me
